<p class="Heading" align=center>Multi-Site Version</p>

<p>
The multi-site option <b>will</b> revolutionize your organization's communication.  With an easily maintainable community of Web Sites, your 
organization can have individual, linked sites for your committees, teams, project groups, whatever!
</p>

<p class="SubHeading" align=center>Who Uses This?</p>
The multi-site system is perfect for any organization with divisions:
	<ul>
		<li>Religious Organizations - Churches, Temples, etc.</li>
		<li>Sports Teams - Divide into team info site, players only site, and alumni site.</li>
		<li>Sports Leagues - Give each team their own individual site in addition to your main home site.</li>
		<li>Businesses - Give each project group or division it's own interactive forum, while maintaining company unity.</li>
		<li><i>Any organization with separate entities.</i></li>
	</ul>

<p class="SubHeading" align=center>Features</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Sites are automatically linked together, so moving from one site to another is simple.</li>
		<li>People can be members of any number of sites.</li>
		<li>Add posts to more than one site at a time.</li>
		<li>Easily create and delete your individual sites.</li>
		<li>You have the <b>top priority</b> with our support team.</li>
	</ul>

